Five sample summaries

[1] 150 In the video, he talked about the importance of reading fiction. Many people choose to read non fiction, because it is straightforward. However reading fiction will have inspired us a lot. Actually Barack Obama chose reading a fiction to learn others feelings (empathy), and how to be comfortable with the notion that the world is complicated and full of grey's.When he read first a hundred pages of book, Frontier Dave Eggers, he was not interested in, because he was not related with the main character, Joge. However when he came to y\\the last part, he was emotional, even though he was not such an emotional person. The character, who has a different background and career, moved him. It described her every emotion, and that kind things trigger his imagination.This is the power of literary fiction. Through reading that, he could get to think more about a person like Joge, empathy. Like a fairtell, people can know more about others' feelings and empathy. Those things were reasons why he recommended reading fiction.                                              
[2]                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       
[3] Tomas Elemens suggests that our rapid access to news and headlines has made us less empathetic toward others. We tend to view people in news stories as distant figures, quickly noting events in our minds before scrolling past them. This behavior coincides with the growing popularity of nonfictions, as we seek to control our lives and improve productivity. However, the world is far more complex than simply uncovering the secrets to efficiency. He believes that reading fiction offers a remedy. He explained the possibility that fiction helps us develop empathy by allowing us to connect with characters and understand diverse perspectives. It also teaches us to accept the complexity of life and recognize that there are no simple answers to profound questions. Through fiction, we learn not only to emphasize with others but also to embrace the uncertainties of the world around us, fostering a deeper understanding of human experience.                                                                                                                                          
[4] Our brains are busier than ever due to the incessant daily news flow, and the world can feel one-dimensional. In such a situation, literary fiction can lead us to another world. In fact, former President Barack Obama has said that he learned from novels his understanding of his role as a citizen and the impact of his role as a citizen.Storytelling helps us not only understand but also feel the complexity of emotions, complexes, and distance from others.He says if you want to raise Albert Einstein as a smart kid, read him fairy tales, and if you want to raise him smarter, read him more fairy tales. Novels help us detach from ourselves and tap into our emotional and artificial side,                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     
[5] The speaker talks about how we are constantly exposed to news and information, which can make us feel detached or overwhelmed. While the media often leaves us feeling distant or indifferent, reading fiction offers a different experience. Books can help us connect emotionally with characters and their stories, which builds empathy. Fiction allows us to imagine what it would be like to live in someone elses shoes and understand their feelings. The speaker gives an example from the novel *Heroes of the Frontier* by Dave Eggers, where they went from not liking the book to becoming deeply invested in the main characters journey. This change happened because fiction helps us immerse ourselves in a story, sparking our imagination and empathy. It reminds us that the world is complicated, but through literature, we can understand others better and feel connected. Fiction is a way to step outside of our own narrow view of the world and experience the emotions and perspectives of others, helping us grow and become more empathetic in a world that often feels disconnected.

Opinions

five sample opinions

[1] I had never consciously thought about the view that fictional stories stimulate our imagination and develop empathy. However, I have loved reading fiction since I was a child, and I have a higher level of empathy than most people. Therefore, Elements' argument is correct, and I agree with his argument. But, I think it's important to not only read fiction, but also non-fiction as well because if we only read fiction, we feel like we are going to lose touch with reality. On the other hand, reading only non-fiction does not help develop empathy. Either way, fiction remains important to us who live in the modern age.                                                                                               
[2] I agree with the idea that it is good to read fiction books. We can experience a lot of things that are impossible in reality from fiction stories. Also, nonfiction books usually are difficult to understand. Fiction books are not as difficult as non fiction books. But, non fiction books are also important, I guess. This is because there are a lot of things that we should think about. For example, we should think about the environment, poverty, our lives and so on. To do so, it is necessary to read nonfiction books to study. In my opinion, we should read both fiction books and nonfiction books.                                                                                                                   
[3] I agree that reading fiction helps us understand others feelings. It also allows us to experience things we could not in real life, which is another appealing aspect. We are so absorbed in the internet that we hardly have time to read books. I think it is sometimes necessary to reduce stress and experience something different from reality through fiction. If I had a child in the future, I want them to read fiction and become kind person.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
[4] Listening to the speakers, I felt that reading fiction books is indeed important. Fiction books are written in a very interesting way to attract the reader's interest, and even though they are fiction, they are not written about things that are far removed from the real world, but are linked to the real world in some way, and there is a lot to learn from them. In particular, I felt that reading books can greatly deepen the way people's emotions move. Non-fiction books are, of course, good, but they often simply state the facts, and are very passive. In that respect, I thought that fiction books can enrich the reader's emotions and allow them to learn about various values by empathizing with the characters.
[5] I learned from listening to the speech that it is very important to empathise with others. Until now I have not read fiction stories. So, at first I was very curious about what it was about. I thought that fiction was very interesting because you can write a little bit of truth, and you can also tell lies. When I was little, I often read fiction stories as picture books, so I wanted to read them again.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
5 Levels: I agree that reading fiction helps us understand others feelings. It also allows us to experience things we could not in real life, which is another appealing aspect. We are so absorbed in the internet that we hardly have time to read books. I think it is sometimes necessary to reduce stress and experience something different from reality through fiction. If I had a child in the future, I want them to read fiction and become kind person. ...
